ENTRY       EC 2.4.2.54                 Enzyme
NAME        beta-ribofuranosylaminobenzene 5'-phosphate synthase;
            beta-RFAP synthase;
            beta-RFA-P synthase;
            AF2089 (gene name);
            MJ1427 (gene name);
            4-(beta-D-ribofuranosyl)aminobenzene 5'-phosphate synthase
CLASS       Transferases;
            Glycosyltransferases;
            Pentosyltransferases
SYSNAME     5-phospho-alpha-D-ribose 1-diphosphate:4-aminobenzoate 5-phospho-beta-D-ribofuranosyltransferase (decarboxylating)
REACTION    5-phospho-alpha-D-ribose 1-diphosphate + 4-aminobenzoate = 4-(beta-D-ribofuranosyl)aniline 5'-phosphate + CO2 + diphosphate [RN:R10337]
ALL_REAC    R10337
SUBSTRATE   5-phospho-alpha-D-ribose 1-diphosphate [CPD:C00119];
            4-aminobenzoate [CPD:C00568]
PRODUCT     4-(beta-D-ribofuranosyl)aniline 5'-phosphate [CPD:C20559];
            CO2 [CPD:C00011];
            diphosphate [CPD:C00013]
COMMENT     Isolated from the archaeon Methanosarcina thermophila and Archaeoglobus fulgidus. The enzyme is involved in biosynthesis of tetrahydromethanopterin in archaea. The activity is dependent on Mg2+ or Mn2+ [1].
